      "id": "PopularPost184989",
      "post_content": "**Random Card Comment**  \n  \nI admit, the 'sleeper' enchantments were one of my favorite cycles. Possibly because when I first started magic, the Urza's cycle was myvery first booster pack purchase. But I think I like the flavor of enchanted statues that 'awaken' when they are threatened. This is an especialyl flavorful card for that. As your enemy comes cloer (your life drops) the statues that adorn you fortress suddenly begin to come to life to repel the intruders and fight back. To top it off, the original type of this card was even 'guardian'. It somewhat puzzles me that unlike [Ivory Guardians](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Guardians) this was errated to just 'soldier' not 'giant soldier'.  \n  \nAnyway, it may not be the easiest slepper to awaken, but it's fairly cheap and I love the flavor, plus it has nostalgia for me because I enjoyed the cycle and still like to make decks around the mechanic for casual paly.",
      "posted_by": "Arachobia",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost184989\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\"><b>Random Card Comment</b><br/><br/>I admit, the 'sleeper' enchantments were one of my favorite cycles. Possibly because when I first started magic, the Urza's cycle was myvery first booster pack purchase. But I think I like the flavor of enchanted statues that 'awaken' when they are threatened. This is an especialyl flavorful card for that. As your enemy comes cloer (your life drops) the statues that adorn you fortress suddenly begin to come to life to repel the intruders and fight back. To top it off, the original type of this card was even 'guardian'. It somewhat puzzles me that unlike <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ivory Guardians\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ivory Guardians\">Ivory Guardians</a> this was errated to just 'soldier' not 'giant soldier'.<br/><br/>Anyway, it may not be the easiest slepper to awaken, but it's fairly cheap and I love the flavor, plus it has nostalgia for me because I enjoyed the cycle and still like to make decks around the mechanic for casual paly.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '184989'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy58281\">Arachobia</span>\r\n                